              xml:id="hamm0038.transcription"
              corresp="#hamm0038.diplomatic #hamm0038.translation">
            <p>Ἐν τῷ καλῷ τόπ<supplied reason="undefined">ῳ</supplied>
               <lb/> μνεισθῇ Ἠλίας <expan><abbr>κ</abbr><ex>αὶ</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>σεβ<supplied reason="undefined">ί</supplied><lb break="no"/>ο</abbr><ex>υ</ex></expan> Μαρία<supplied reason="undefined">ς</supplied> Βοσ<surplus>σ</surplus>τρ<supplied reason="undefined">ην</supplied>ῆς<lb/> μετὰ τῶν ἀγαπόντων αὐτο<supplied reason="undefined">ύς</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              xml:id="hamm0038.translation"
              corresp="#hamm0038.diplomatic #hamm0038.transcription">
            <p>In this beautiful place may <persName xml:lang="x-Semitic " ref="persons.xml#hamm0038p01">Elias </persName> be remembered, and <persName ref="persons.xml#hamm0038p02">Mary </persName>
               <rs type="ethnicon">of Bostra</rs>, his <rs type="family">wife</rs>, with all who love them.</p>
         </div>
